result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob Michael Brauer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Cts. 1 & 4.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea. Court reviews collateral consequences of felony conviction, possible penalties. Defendant must have a DNA sample on file with the State of Wisconsin and pay a DNA surcharge. State/Defense are ready to proceed to sentencing without the benefit of a PSI.  Victim makes statement.  State gives sentencing recommendation, makes statement.  Defense gives sentencing argument.  Court makes statement, imposes sentence.  Bond is no longer in effect.
